Pupils in KwaZulu-Natal have seen it all in the last couple of years but they were not deterred. eNCA’s Nqobile Madlala caught up with some elated matriculants, and filed this report. #DStv403 DURBAN - Pupils in KwaZulu-Natal have seen it all in the last couple of years. COVID-19 lockdowns, the 2021 July riots, devastating floods and of course rolling blackouts. READ: 2022 Matric Results | Umalusi gives release the thumbs-up But they were not deterred. This has been reflected in the 2022 IEB matric results, with two of Durban's private schools -- Reddam House and Curro College -- producing a 100 percent pass rate. * eNCA’s Nqobile Madlala reports.